SIMPLE: holiness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Holiness
<hw>Ho"li*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>h⟦amac⟧lignes</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state or quality
of being holy; perfect moral integrity or purity; freedom from sin;
sanctity; innocence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Who is like thee, glorious in <qex>holiness</qex>!</q>
<rj><qau>Ex. xv. 11.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state of being hallowed, or consecrated to God
or to his worship; sacredness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Israel was <qex>holiness</qex> unto the Lord.</q>
<rj><qau>Jer.ii.3.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>His holiness</b></col>, <cd>a title of the pope; --
formerly given also to Greek bishops and Greek emperors.</cd></cs></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Piety; devotion; godliness; sanctity; sacredness;
righteousness.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Holing</ent>⟦br⟧
